title: Frederick Forsyth - The Odessa File (Unabridged)
description:
Audio Books : Thriller : Other quality : English

Unabridged, read by Bob Peck

A package of documents, containing a list of names, arrives anonymously at the Ministry of Justice in Bonn in 1964. 

Frederick Forsyth's bestselling thriller features the consequent life-and-death hunt for a notorious Nazi criminal, against a background of international arms deals.
